window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>In </b><b><i>Trapping Zero</i></b><b> (book 4), a terrorist cell in the Mideast gains a new, fanatic leader, one intent on orchestrating what would be the deadliest attack on American soil. Can Agent Zero uncover the plot and stop him in time?</b></p> <p>Although Agent Zeroâ€™s daughters are home safely, the mental anguish from their experience weighs heavy on their small family. Zero, working to be a good father and to repair the damage, decides the time has come to undergo surgery to regain all of his memories. But will it work?</p> <p>In the midst of it all, he is again thrust into the line of duty as a US embassy is destroyed in the Mideast and as an experimental new weapon is uncovered. But without his memories, with some of his own CIA allies intent on his destruction, whom can he really trust?</p> <p><i>Trapping Zero</i> (book 4) is a pause-resisting espionage thriller that will keep you listening late into the night.&nbsp;</p>"; 
